        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated. The global prodcution of paper and pulp has been derived from FAO (2013) "Pulp and paper capacities (link: http://www.fao.org/docrep/018/i3353t/i3353t.pdf, accessed 20150930). Sludge from paper and pulp production is calculated as the average between 40 and 50 kg of dry mass per tonnes of paper from Hagelqvist (2013) "Sludge from pulp and paper mills for biogas prodcution) (link : http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:603009/FULLTEXT01.pdf&amp;sa=U&amp;ei=T0FOU4byPMfOsgar5YGgCQ&amp;ved=0CB0QFjAA&amp;usg=AFQjCNEX-zId539_0tE-9pE_R9JMV9eINg, accessed 20150930). Of the total sludge 20% is assumed to go to landfill (from: Series on Emission Scenario Documents Pulp, Paper and Board Industry, OECD 2009. Link: https://books.google.ch/books?id=0pRsBAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA51&amp;lpg=PA51&amp;dq=paper+sludge+landfill+agriculture&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=V2IWi69XjP&amp;sig=CgziYiNJDLjP6FYiKKXxOLHE7Ow&amp;hl=de&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0CFYQ6AEwB2oVChMI0ejH3KeeyAIVxe0UCh2TLAr9#v=onepage&amp;q=paper%20sludge%20landfill%20agriculture&amp;f=false, accessed 20150930)</productionVolumeComment>
